Job Description 
The Analytics Research Department within the Advanced Analytics Center of Expertise (COE) is looking for highly motivated, collaborative individuals to join our growing team. Our mission is to identify and analyze strategic opportunities to improve GMâ€™s profitability, increase operational efficiency and provide customer insights. Application focus areas are enterprise-wide including customer analytics, finance, marketing, product development, revenue management, quality, and supply chain and logistics. 
This position requires mathematical expertise, creative problem solving, cross-functional communication, teamwork, technical documentation, and presentation and project/technical leadership skills. Candidates should demonstrate an exceptional ability to adapt to ambiguous business objectives, and clearly communicate the value of business analytics to a non-technical audience. 
Additional Job Description 
Requirements: 
Ph.D. preferred / MS required with 1-3 years experience in a technical discipline, such as operations research, applied mathematics, statistics, decision science, econometrics, engineering, marketing, or artificial intelligence/machine learning 
Excellent collaboration skills with project teams, management, customers, and experts 
Excellent oral and written communication skills with a particular strength in explaining technical concepts to non-technical audiences 
Ability to quickly learn and adapt skills to work on various projects in different technical and functional areas 
Ability and willingness to contribute on multiple levels including: data preparation, algorithm development, documentation, programming, project management, conducting experiments, and interacting with clients 
Interested in systems-level modeling and analysis of complex problems that may be poorly defined and cross functional, and may have uncertainty, multiple objectives, or decisions involving trade-offs 
Proficient in one or more of the following (or equivalent): AMPL/GAMS, AnyLogic, C/C++, CPLEX/Gurobi, Java, LISREL, OpenCL, OpenCV, Python, R, SQL, SAS, SPSS, SmartPLS, Stata, TensorFlow, Weka, GPU/parallel programming experience 
